p: In terms of nepetalactone production, the CR3 chemotype contained 68.2% E, Z-nepetalactone and 25.6% Z, E-nepetalactone while CR9 contained 90.1% Z, E-nepetalactone and less than 0.5% E, Z-nepetalactone and the commercial N. cataria essential oil contained 24.4% Z, E-nepetalactone and 62.8% E, Z-nepetalactone (Table 1; Fig. 2). Other minor volatile essential oil components included in catnip samples CR3, CR9 and the commercial oil are β-pinene at <0.5%, 0.58% and 0.57% respectively, β-caryophyllene at 1.57%, 4.72% and 8.11% respectively, humulene at <0.5%, 0.51%, and 0.58% respectively and caryophyllene oxide at 1.27%, 5.79%, and 1.56% respectively. Compounds detected in just the commercial sample were α-pinene and carvone at concentrations of 0.52% and 0.67% respectively (all as rel. % of total essential oil).
